& =\frac{1}{g_{m 1}} \| r_{O 1} \tag{6.73}
\end{align*}
$$

For the PMOS version, the equivalent is depicted in Fig. 6.34(c), and we write

$$
\begin{align*}
R_{Y} & =\frac{v_{Y}}{i_{Y}}  \tag{6.74}\\
& =\left(g_{m 2} v_{Y}+\frac{v_{Y}}{r_{O 1}}\right) \frac{1}{i_{Y}}  \tag{6.75}\\
