Due to the lower mobility of holes (Chapter 2), PMOS devices exhibit inferior performance compared to NMOS transistors. For instance, Eq. (6.46) shows that the transconductance of a PMOS device is lower for a given drain current. Therefore, we prefer using NMOS transistors whenever feasible.

